******
[2]
Date: Mon 25 Jun 2018
Source: WSOC-TV [edited]
https://www.wsoctv.com/news/local/possible-e-coli-cases-linked-to-alexander-co-restaurant-rise-to-100/776833163


The [Alexander County] Health Department said about 100 people have reported getting sick after a possible outbreak of enteropathogenic _E. coli_ at Mexico Viejo in Alexander County, NC. One person tested positive for enteropathogenic _E. coli_, or EPEC, after dining at the restaurant on Highway 90 in Taylorsville, NC, health officials said. On [Fri 22 Jun 2018], health officials reported 30 possible cases, but that number grew to about 100 on [Mon 25 Jun 2018].

Alexander County health director Leeanne Whisnant said environmental health specialists were sent to inspect the restaurant on [Fri 22 Jun 2018].

Enteropathogenic _E. coli_ is a bacteria that causes severe stomach cramps, diarrhea that is often bloody, vomiting, and sometimes a low-grade fever, according to health officials.

The restaurant is being cooperative, officials said. Officials are asking customers who ate at Mexico Viejo on [Wed 20 Jun 2018] and have experienced symptoms to call the Health Department.

We [WSOC-TV] obtained the last 3 inspection reports for Mexico Viejo. Each time the restaurant was given a score of 96, which is an A.

